comments.body:
This is most likely caused by a JPA 1.0 API Jar (Java Persistence API) on the classpath, JPA 2.0 is used in Eucalyptus (with Hibernate)

To build Eucalyptus 3.3.0, the maint/3.3/testing branch of the libraries repository [1] can be used (with the 3.3.0 tag from the eucalyptus repository)

Feel free to ask questions on the #eucalyptus (user) or #eucalyptus-devel (development) channel on IRC/freenode or via the Eucalyptus Users euca-users@eucalyptus.com (user) or develop@eucalyptus.com (development) mailing lists.

[1] https://github.com/eucalyptus/eucalyptus-cloud-libs

Thank you very much for your reply. Indeed, I download my own JPA version becase the testing branch compile complain about the error below. I'm not sure whether I misconfig the classpath or testing branch didn't include JPA needed. After I delete my own JPA and use testing branch, make command exit by error.
